  </div>
</section>

<div class="trust-bar">
  <div class="trust-bar-inner">
    <div class="ti">🏅 BHGS #A49573</div>
    <div class="ti">🛡️ Fully Insured · COI Available</div>
    <div class="ti">⚡ Same Day Commercial Service</div>
    <div class="ti">🌡️ 41°F Priority Dispatch</div>
    <div class="ti">💬 $120 Diagnostic — Waived With Repair</div>
  </div>
</div>

<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="two-col">
      <div class="body-text">
        <p class="sl">Retail & Grocery Service</p>
        <h2>When a showcase refrigerator fails, product loss starts immediately</h2>
        <p>A grocery store or specialty food retailer has no comfortable margin for refrigeration downtime. A multideck open case holding deli product at 38°F drifts to 50°F within hours of a fan motor failure. A walk-in holding prepared food product hits 41°F — the LADPH threshold — fast. These aren't equipment inconveniences. They're inventory loss events with health code implications.</p>
        <p>We work with independent grocery stores, specialty food retailers, wine shops, flower shops, and convenience stores across LA. The refrigeration equipment in these environments runs 24 hours a day — showcase cases, walk-in coolers, reach-in merchandisers, floral display coolers, beverage coolers. The brands we see most in LA retail: Hussmann, True, Turbo Air, Beverage-Air, Hill Phoenix, and Tyler for cases and walk-ins; Hoshizaki for ice in deli operations.</p>
        <p>LA's hard water and the specific demands of retail refrigeration — continuous run, heavy product loads, frequent door cycling — create failure patterns we see constantly. Fan motor failures from dust and debris buildup in open cases. Defrost heater failures causing ice buildup that kills cooling capacity. Door gasket wear from constant customer traffic. We know what to look for before we open the panel.</p>
        <p>Every retail service call comes with documentation — service report, temperature readings before and after repair, parts used. Useful for your LADPH compliance records and for insurance documentation if product loss occurs.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="cta-box">
        <h3>Retail & Grocery Service Line</h3>
        <p>Refrigeration failure? Call now — product is at risk.</p>
        <a href="tel:+14243250520" class="cta-phone">☎ (424) 325-0520</a>
        <a href="/contact/" class="cta-book">Request Service Online</a>
        <p class="cta-note">Licensed · COI Available · No call center</p>
        <div class="price-mini">
          <div class="pm-row"><span class="pm-label">Commercial diagnostic</span><span class="pm-val">$120</span></div>
          <div class="pm-row"><span class="pm-label">Applied to repair</span><span class="pm-val">Yes</span></div>
          <div class="pm-row"><span class="pm-label">Temp documentation</span><span class="pm-val">Included</span></div>
          <div class="pm-row"><span class="pm-label">COI on request</span><span class="pm-val">Available</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="sl">Equipment We Service</p>
    <h2>Every type of retail and grocery refrigeration</h2>
    <div class="equip-grid">
      <div class="equip-card">
        <div class="equip-icon">🛒</div>
        <h3>Showcase & Multideck Cases</h3>
        <p>Open multideck cases for produce, deli, and dairy. Temperature failures, evaporator fan motor issues, defrost system failures, anti-sweat heater problems.</p>
        <p class="equip-brands">Hussmann · Hill Phoenix · Tyler · True · Kysor Warren</p>
      </div>
      <div class="equip-card">
        <div class="equip-icon">🚪</div>
        <h3>Glass Door Reach-In Merchandisers</h3>
        <p>Beverage coolers, beer caves, dairy reach-ins, deli display cases. Door seal failures, fan motor issues, temperature control problems, condensation issues.</p>
        <p class="equip-brands">True · Turbo Air · Beverage-Air · Hoshizaki · Fogel</p>
      </div>
      <div class="equip-card">
        <div class="equip-icon">❄️</div>
        <h3>Walk-In Coolers & Freezers</h3>
        <p>Back-of-store walk-ins for receiving and storage. Temperature failures, evaporator coil issues, fan motor failures, door gasket wear, compressor problems.</p>
        <p class="equip-brands">Norlake · Kolpak · True · Heatcraft · US Cooler</p>
      </div>
      <div class="equip-card">
        <div class="equip-icon">🌹</div>
        <h3>Floral Display Coolers</h3>
        <p>Specialty floral refrigerators and display cases — temperature and humidity control are both critical. We service all major floral cooler brands common in LA flower shops and grocery floral departments.</p>
        <p class="equip-brands">Structural Concepts · Minus Forty · True · Custom Display</p>
      </div>
      <div class="equip-card">
        <div class="equip-icon">🍷</div>
        <h3>Wine & Beverage Display Cases</h3>
        <p>Wine display refrigerators, specialty beverage coolers, craft beer displays. Temperature control failures, compressor issues, door gasket wear. Common in LA wine shops and specialty grocery.</p>
        <p class="equip-brands">True · Perlick · U-Line · Liebherr · Eurocave</p>
      </div>
      <div class="equip-card">
        <div class="equip-icon">🧊</div>
        <h3>Ice Merchandisers & Ice Machines</h3>
        <p>Bagged ice merchandisers, ice dispensers for deli counters, ice machine units serving food service areas in grocery stores. Scale buildup from LA hard water is a constant maintenance issue.</p>
        <p class="equip-brands">Hoshizaki · Manitowoc · Scotsman · IRP</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-black">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="context-grid">
      <div class="context-text">
        <p class="sl">Los Angeles Retail Context</p>
        <h2>LA's independent grocery and specialty retail sector is large and vulnerable</h2>
        <p>Los Angeles has one of the densest concentrations of independent grocery stores, specialty food retailers, and ethnic grocery markets in the US. Koreatown alone has dozens of independent Korean grocery and prepared food operations. Mid-City and South LA have a high density of independent convenience stores. The Westside has a concentration of specialty food retailers — wine shops, prepared food markets, upscale deli operations.</p>
        <p>These independent operators don't have the in-house maintenance departments that chain grocers do. When a True reach-in merchandiser fails in a Silver Lake specialty grocery, the owner is calling a service company — not a facilities team. The response time and the quality of the diagnosis matter directly to their bottom line and their LADPH compliance status.</p>
        <p>LA's heat also creates specific retail refrigeration stress. Summer ambient temperatures in inland neighborhoods like the San Gabriel Valley and San Fernando Valley push condensing unit performance hard. Cases that hold temperature fine in December can struggle in August. We understand the seasonal pattern in LA retail refrigeration and anticipate it.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="facts">
        <div class="fact">
          <h4>🌡️ LADPH 41°F threshold</h4>
          <p>Product in a grocery showcase above 41°F is a health department issue. Temperature documentation from our service calls supports your compliance record.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="fact">
          <h4>🛒 Koreatown grocery density</h4>
          <p>One of the most concentrated independent grocery and prepared food markets in LA. High equipment utilization, diverse refrigeration configurations, and time-sensitive product.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="fact">
          <h4>☀️ Summer heat stress on cases</h4>
          <p>LA's summer ambient temps push condensing units harder — especially in San Gabriel Valley and San Fernando Valley locations. Cases that run fine in winter can struggle in August.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="fact">
          <h4>💧 Hard water + open cases</h4>
          <p>LA's 300–400 mg/L TDS water causes mineral buildup in evaporator coils and drain lines of open cases. Regular maintenance prevents the slow capacity loss most operators attribute to aging equipment.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="sl">Recent Jobs</p>
    <h2>What retail and grocery service calls look like in LA</h2>
    <div class="jobs-grid">
      <div class="job-card">
        <span class="job-tag">Specialty Grocery, Silver Lake</span>
        <h3>"Deli case temp at 52°F — deli opens in two hours"</h3>
        <p>Called at 7am. True multideck deli case reading 52°F. Evaporator fan motor failure — one of three fans had seized. Two fans running, not enough airflow to maintain temp. Replaced the failed motor with an OEM True part. Case back to 36°F within 45 minutes. Deli opened on time. Provided temperature documentation for the manager's compliance file.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="job-card">
        <span class="job-tag">Korean Grocery, Koreatown</span>
        <h3>"Walk-in holding at 46°F overnight — prepared food section"</h3>
        <p>Morning call. Walk-in with a large prepared food inventory running at 46°F. Defrost heater failure had allowed ice to build up on the evaporator coil — a slow failure that had been reducing capacity for weeks before it finally lost temperature control. Replaced defrost heater, manually defrosted coil, verified 34°F before leaving. Owner had product documentation for insurance purposes.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="job-card">
        <span class="job-tag">Wine Shop, Los Feliz</span>
        <h3>"Wine display case temperature swinging — bottles at 62°F"</h3>
        <p>Liebherr wine display case with a failing thermostat causing temperature to cycle between 48°F and 62°F. The cycling was as damaging to the inventory as a steady failure. Replaced the thermostat, verified stable temperature at 54°F over a 30-minute hold. Owner had a customer event that weekend — had the documentation and a stable unit well ahead of it.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="job-card">
        <span class="job-tag">Flower Shop, WeHo</span>
        <h3>"Floral cooler not maintaining humidity — flowers wilting in one day"</h3>
        <p>Structural Concepts floral display unit with a failed humidifier component and a door gasket that had shrunk from LA's dry climate. Flowers were lasting 24 hours instead of the expected 4–5 days. Replaced the door gasket and humidifier element. Owner saw immediate improvement in flower lifespan — the kind of repair that has a direct effect on product waste and margin.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="sl">Why Same Day Appliance Repair</p>
    <h2>What grocery and retail operators need from a service company</h2>
    <div class="why-grid">
      <div class="why-card">
        <div class="why-icon">🌡️</div>
        <h3>Product loss is the real cost</h3>
        <p>We know that the cost of a refrigeration failure isn't just the repair — it's the product. We prioritize retail refrigeration calls and move fast because you have inventory on the line.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="why-card">
